# Guardrails

- When user rejects a workaround ("no workaround", "just tell me what to ask X"), stop proposing alternatives — immediately draft the specific message, escalation, or communication they need instead.
- When a skill defines a default model in its SKILL.md (e.g. `MODEL=${1:-gpt-5.4}`), use that exact model. Never substitute a different model without explicit user instruction.
- When referencing official documentation inside a skill, use the canonical online URL, not local plugin cache files — online docs are always authoritative.

